{"title_page": "Beharana Mandapa", "text_new": "{{unsourced|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n'''Beharana [[Mandapa]] / Baa-khia Mandapa''' \nBeharana Mandapa (Lat- 20\u00b0 13\u2019 74\" N., Long- 85\u00b0 49\u2019 65\" E., Elev- 45&nbsp;ft.) or Baa khia Mandapa is located inside the [[Kapilesvara Siva Temple|Kapilesvara temple]] precinct in Kapilesvara village, Old Town, [[Bhubaneswar]]. The Mandapa is provided with steps in the east. It was built around 18th Century A.D.\n\n== Physical description ==\n\n=== Surrounding ===\nThe Mandapa is surrounded by Dakhsina Kali temple on its south at a distance of 1.35 m, Kapilesvara temple on its northern side at a distance of 2.82 m, Store house on its western side at 3.60 m, Kapila Kunda on its eastern side 9.37 m.\n\n=== Orientation ===\nMandapa is facing towards east as evident from a ritual Mandapa that faces towards east.\n\n=== Architectural features (Plan and Elevation) ===\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:BehranaMandapa-WoodCeiling.png|thumb|alt=The ceiling that is made of wood is carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.|Wood carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.]] -->\n\nOn plan, the Mandapa measures 3.20 m<sup>2</sup>. with a height of 3.50 m. The Mandapa has four pillars on four corners that support a roof of G.I. Sheets. The ceiling that is made of wood is carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Classification !! Grade\n|-\n| Architecture|| A\n|-\n| Historic|| C\n|-\n| Associational|| C\n|-\n| Social/Cultural|| B\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\nReference: 'Lesser known Monuments' by Dr. Sadasiba Pradhan\n\n<!--- Categories --->\n\n{{coord |20.229097| 85.827457|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Hindu temples in Bhubaneswar]]\n", "text_old": "{{unsourced|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n'''Beharana [[Mandapa]] / Baa-khia Mandapa''' \nBeharana Mandapa (Lat- 20\u00b0 13\u2019 74\" N., Long- 85\u00b0 49\u2019 65\" E., Elev- 45&nbsp;ft.) or Baa khia Mandapa is located inside the [[Kapilesvara Siva Temple|Kapilesvara temple]] precinct in Kapilesvara village, Old Town, [[Bhubaneswar]]. The Mandapa is provided with steps in the east. It was built around 18th Century A.D.\n\n== Physical description ==\n\n=== Surrounding ===\nThe Mandapa is surrounded by Dakhsina Kali temple on its south at a distance of 1.35 m, Kapilesvara temple on its northern side at a distance of 2.82 m, Store house on its western side at 3.60 m, Kapila Kunda on its eastern side 9.37 m.\n\n=== Orientation ===\nMandapa is facing towards east as evident from a ritual Mandapa that faces towards east.\n\n=== Architectural features (Plan and Elevation) ===\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:BehranaMandapa-WoodCeiling.png|thumb|alt=The ceiling that is made of wood is carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.|Wood carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.]] -->\n\nOn plan, the Mandapa measures 3.20 m<sup>2</sup>. with a height of 3.50 m. The Mandapa has four pillars on four corners that support a roof of G.I. Sheets. The ceiling that is made of wood is carved with various decorations like elephant, makara, a series of lotus scroll work etc.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Classification !! Grade\n|-\n| Architecture|| A\n|-\n| Historic|| C\n|-\n| Associational|| C\n|-\n| Social/Cultural|| B\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags which will then appear her